body_html:
So, if you import random modules in tensorflow, you will have access to private symbols.

Just a note to say that this isn't the case for imports in tf.keras, because the underlying files only contain public symbols (they're separate API-only files).

body:
> So, if you import random modules in tensorflow, you will have access to private symbols. 

Just a note to say that this isn't the case for imports in `tf.keras`, because the underlying files only contain public symbols (they're separate API-only files).
